{
  "stem": "3022.5",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "And at that time in April, we could hear heavy artillery guns from far.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "We were taken on a march.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "There was about 2,700 people that started out on the march.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "On the third day of the march, there was only about 900 of us left. 1,800 were left in the ditches alongside the road.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "It was about a 60-mile stretch that we covered in those three days.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 43,
      "text": "My friend who was with me-- his name was Oscar Klausenstock, and now presently Dr.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 44,
      "text": "Oscar Klausenstock-- developed a temperature.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 45,
      "text": "And he said he wasn't going to make it anymore.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 46,
      "text": "He couldn't.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So at one of the stops, my father said, I should tell you what.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "People were laying down and dying.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He says, lay down, and we'll cover you as if you were dead.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And we covered him with branches, and he laid in the ditch.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And the convoy marched on.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He was left over there.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "On the 26th of April, the third day of the march, the SS major of the convoy and the eldest of the prisoners passed by the convoy on a motorcycle.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "There was a bolt in it.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And they went.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "They left, and they came back about a half an hour later.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And they took us to a clearing.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "They announced that we're surrounded by American troops, and each and every SS man should take about five or six prisoners and go to find a hiding place.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And when the glorious German army will conquer the Americans, we will reassemble.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "What it was, it was a ruse that was planned between the SS major and the camp commandant, the head of the prisoners.",
      "word_count": 23
    }
  ],
